<doc id="449403" wikidata="Q329028" url="?curid=449403" title="Provinces of Angola">
<text>Angola is divided into twenty-one provinces, known in Portuguese as &quot;províncias&quot;. On 14 August 2024, Angola&#x27;s National Assembly approved a law to create three new provinces: 
* Cuando Cubango Province was divided into Cuando Province and Cubango Province; 
* Icolo e Bengo Province was separated from Luanda Province; and
* Moxico Leste Province was separated from Moxico Province. 

This law went into effect with its publication in the official gazette of Angola on 5 September 2024, and are expected to become operational in 2025. The former eighteen provinces are tabulated below:
